question:
For a real number $a$, let $F_a(x) = \sum_{n \geq 1} n^a e^{2n} x^{n^2}$ for $0 \leq x < 1$.
Find a real number $c$ such that
\begin{align*}
& \lim_{x \to 1^-} F_a(x) e^{-1/(1-x)} = 0 \qquad \mbox{for all $a < c$, and} \\
& \lim_{x \to 1^-} F_a(x) e^{-1/(1-x)} = \infty \qquad \mbox{for all $a > c$.}
\end{align*}

\end{itemize}

\end{document}z

descriptive_long.question:
For a real number $realparam$, let $seriesfunc(variablex) = \sum_{indexvar \geq 1} indexvar^{realparam} e^{2 indexvar} variablex^{indexvar^2}$ for $0 \leq variablex < 1$.
Find a real number $genconst$ such that
\begin{align*}
& \lim_{variablex \to 1^-} seriesfunc(variablex) e^{-1/(1-variablex)} = 0 \qquad \mbox{for all $realparam < genconst$, and} \\
& \lim_{variablex \to 1^-} seriesfunc(variablex) e^{-1/(1-variablex)} = \infty \qquad \mbox{for all $realparam > genconst$.}
\end{align*}

\end{itemize}

\end{document}z

